txt.en: In the shadows of the Harrowdale, you have encountered a vicious Warg. In the absence of their warriors, Ellen Fremedon and her people are ill-equipped to deal with these savage creatures. You decide to strike first against the Wargs lest their hunger draws them closer to the innocent people of Underharrow.
You have defeated Wargs lurking too near to Underharrow and protected the defenceless people of Kingstead.
You have defeated many Wargs in the Harrowdale, freeing the nigh-defenceless people of Underharrow from fear as they make ready to travel to Dunharrow with Ã‰owyn.
You have not yet slain enough Wargs.
Harrowing Wargs can be found throughout the Harrowdale.\n\nYou have encountered a vicious Warg while exploring the Harrowdale. You should defeat more of its kind to protect the people of Underharrow.
Ellen Fremedon struggles to care for Underharrow and Kingstead's refugees, but just outside town, Wargs wait patiently to close their jaws on the defenceless settlement.
